                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "body": "[~wesmckinn] I don't think that will solve this problem. The _original_ dataframe (when converted to an arrow Table) had a trivial RangeIndex (starting at 0, step of 1), so the optimization would have been correctly applied according to that logic. \r\n\r\nIt is only when a Table is sliced or splitted (in row groups, and then reading a single row group instead of the full table) that the RangeIndex metadata get \"out of date\" and no longer match the new (subsetted) arrow Table.\r\n\r\nSee also ARROW-5427 for a summary issue I made on this topic.",
